Product name: Antique Edwardian earrings 1900-1920's Vintage Amethyst Pearl Art Deco Gatsby Flapper Long dangle screw back fitting Platinin/Platinon
Description:
A very pretty and dainty pair of Antique earrings from the late Edwardian to early Art Deco era 1910-20's. 
They come from my personal collection of antique and Art Deco costume jewellery and I think it is time to pass them on rather than have them languish in a box!
They were probably made in France and are a fine white metal called Platinon or sometimes Platinin which is an alloy used to imitate Platinum.  It is hard and strong just like Platinum and can be used for fine work.  
They have faux pearls to the top and natural Amethyst beads on the bottom.
These wonderful earrings have the original screw fittings which can be worn by people with or without pierced ears. 
IDENTIFICATION : Stamped 'Platinon' on each screw fitting.
MATERIALS : White metal.  Faux pearl.  Natural Amethyst.
MEASUREMENTS :  Top of screw fitting to bottom of drop is 5.2cms long
CONDITION : They are in very good vintage condition with an antique patina.

Product name: Vintage Glass Insulator Set / Sage Green Glass Insulator / Dark Olive Green Insulator / Artichoke Green Glass, Heavy Glass Mushroom, CD 408
Description:
Vintage Glass Insulator Set / Sage Green Glass Insulator / Dark Olive Green Insulator / Artichoke Green Glass / Heavy Glass Mushroom, CD 408 
************************************
These glass insulators were installed on the telephone poles in my native village in the early 60's. I loved the graphic appearance of the wooden poles attached by on to another through long slender cables that made communication possible through long distances. The glass insulator mounted on top of the horizontal cross arms always made me think of mushrooms and shaped the fantastic image of the streets I played on as a small child.  Nowadays the purpose of the beautiful wood poles has disappeared and they were replaced by modern concrete poles that lack the personality and uniqueness of wood. My dad somehow managed to save the glass insulators and I hope you will give them a good retirement. 
MEASUREMENTS: 
height ~11 cm ( ~ 4.3 inch ) 
base: Ø ~7.8 cm ( ~ 3 inch )
MARKINGS: SL 2 STAS 810-52 
CONDITION: The glass insulators are in fair to near mint condition with some small chips on the wire groove ridge or on the base. Glass insulators are hand washed by me, still I didn't insist too much on getting all the rust and signs of age off the glass because I like the look and feeling of the ages that have past to be seen on them. However if you like the glass insulators to look like new you can wash them better and get off any trace of rust. I will take a set of random insulators. 
This beautiful set of Sage Green Glass Insulator would look great on your windowsill, on your desk as a paperweight, in your library as bookends or even as a doorstop in your beautiful home. You can also use them in your garden as an accent piece or for lining your walkway. The options of reusing these beautiful pieces of heavy glass are endless. 
************************************
Please select the nr of insulators wanted in the drop down menu right under the price. Shipping cost can vary depending on the number of insulators bought, I will refund the overcharged shipping on the smaller sets. 
Shipping to the US will be somewhere at 25 US for 2 insulators, 30 US for 4 insulators and 36 US for 5 insulators. 
Shipping in most of the world should be around 30 US for 2 insulators, 40 US for 4 insulators, 50  for 5 insulators. 
I will refund accordingly to the real shipping costs of the package. 
 
************************************
Please ask any questions you may have before making a purchase!
I will be happy to answer any questions and send more photos if needed!
Items are sold as they are so please be sure this item is for you before buying!
Please note that colors may vary slightly depending on the monitor used.
Thank you for viewing.

Description:
Kemner Design proudly presents the KD Starter series of precision spin tops.  The KD Starter collection of metal spinning tops have a simple design yet are fun and functional.  These spin tops are lightweight (13 g)  and easy to spin making them ideal for those just starting out or the everyday carry (EDC) enthusiasts.  If you are looking for a pocket top, the KD Starter's lightweight and simple design maybe of particular interest to you.  The KD Starter was crafted on a CNC lathe followed by hand finishing and knurling of its stem on a manual lathe.  
Kemner Design's KD Starter series of metal spinning tops make a for a fun and unique gift idea.  Easter is right around the corner, so why not check out pur fun and colorful spin tops as a candy free alternative for the easter basket.  
While spin times will vary with practice and experience level, the starter has an average spin time of 2-4 minutes.  During performance testing I was able to achieve an spin time of 5 minutes.  All Kemner Design tops are designed, crafted and finished in my shop.  I personally test all my spin tops for performance prior to shipping them to you.  The KD starter comes with a personalized owners card that proudly displays the name of the top, birth date, material and bearing used, serial number and maker’s signature.  Whether it be a new addition to your collection or a possible gift idea, you will not be dissapointed with this top.  
Tops can have multiple functions; they can be used for stress relief, educational purposes, display or to play with.  Whatever your choice, this top will provide you with hours of enjoyment.   These solid metal tops are designed to last many lifetimes and can be passed down from generation to generation.

Product name: Wubbers Wire Looping Pliers - For wrapped loops and eyepins - PLR-1350
Description:
Wubbers has done it again!! This time it is the WIRE LOOPING PLIERS for wrapping beads and making eyepins perfect every time!! Never before has there been a pair of pliers that can do so much and so easy to learn. 
The instructional CD, included with each pair, gives basic step-by-step instructions that anyone can master in no time. The unique jaw shape and size provides for a consistent finish.  
Visit the link below for the designer's complete description and to watch a demonstration video for this new, must-have wire looping plier:
http://www.wubbers.com/prod-looping.html
Wrapped Loops
The Wubbers Looping Pliers are designed to work with 20-gauge wire and will make perfectly round loops with an inside diameter of approximately 2.2mm. When wrapping a loop on the second end of a bead, there is no need to "guesstimate" how much space to leave, because these pliers automatically measure for you. The Wubbers Looping Pliers will hold your work securely as you wind the wire around the neck. That means no more slipping and sliding as you work, and no more twisted or lopsided loops. Also important, the edges of the jaws are carefully rounded to prevent marring and are shaped to support as you wrap, keeping your work straight. 
Eye Pins
With the Wubbers Looping Pliers, you will be able to make perfect eye pins quickly and effortlessly. They enable you to "break the neck" (center your loop over the wire) without distorting your loop in the least.
Use with 20 and 22 gauge soft wire. Overall length 5 1/2".
We ship via Priority Mail with Tracking, so you should have your package in 2 to 3 days.

It allows the bracelet to be adjustable and the stamping to have a nice deep impression. There is a much lower rate of skin reaction with pure aluminum than with sterling silver. It will never tarnish, discolor or rust. It does not leave green marks on your skin like other metals. Aluminum is a metal that is easy to maintain. It polishes to a nice shine with a polishing cloth. The cuff measures 6” and is adjustable to fit nearly any wrist.
